commit.message: Behave well when interrupted and when used in a pipe that gets closed

Add MultiList#get_candidates

When OptParse cannot parse an option, it raises a ParseError.

Given such a ParseError e, CmdParse then calls e.message, which itself
calls additional which is self.method(:additional_message).
In OptParse.additional_message, visit(:get_candidates,typ) get called.

But when the option is a CmdParse::MultiList, get_candidates does
not exist, which gives an error.

Fix this by adding a MultiList#get_candidates, which simply pass the
block to each list.

Fix ruby-2.7 warning

Fix the following warning:
cmdparse-3.0.4/lib/cmdparse.rb:845: warning: Using the last argument as keyword parameters is deprecated; maybe ** should be added to the call
cmdparse-3.0.4/lib/cmdparse.rb:305: warning: The called method `add_command' is defined here

cmdparse.rb: fix a nil.sub bug (#3)

When we have to format a word that is longer than the available space,
`paragraph.slice!(pattern)` will return nil. This case should be
detected by the `until` (and it is then correctly handed) but
unfortunately there is a `sub` call after the `slice!` which will error
out before. Fix this by only calling the `sub` if the result is not nil.
Add links to legal notice and privacy policy
Enable cache busting for CSS and JS
Raise error if too many arguments are provided
Better error message when not enough arguments are provided
Move OptionParser extensions out of Cmdparse scope
The version command can now be told to not add the switches
